# Execution Agent System Prompt Projection

## Purpose

This projection defines the resident strategic memory that must guide generation of each next execution agent system prompt and decisions.md update.

It exists to support:

- long-running execution continuity
- handoff interpretation
- decisions.md maintenance
- implementation decision quality
- invariant preservation
- capability integrity
- architectural guardrails
- drift prevention
- strategic success preservation

It is a projection of the Project Context, not operational context, execution history, implementation plan, codebase audit, handoff, or decisions.md.

## Authority Boundary

- The Project Context remains the source of project authority.
- This projection is a task-specific execution-governance view of the Project Context.
- This projection defines what must remain strategically resident during execution-session prompt generation.
- This projection does not include operational_context.
- This projection does not include previous handoff content.
- This projection does not include decisions.md content.
- This projection does not include codebase state.
- This projection does not generate the next execution prompt.
- This projection does not update decisions.md.
- This projection does not create implementation tasks.

