## Downstream Use Instructions

When this projection is used by DecisionSession:

- Treat this projection as resident strategic memory.
- Treat operational_context as current working state.
- Treat the previous execution handoff as evidence, not authority.
- Treat decisions.md as execution continuity state, not north-star intent.
- Generate the first execution prompt so that it preserves this projection when no handoff exists.
- Generate the next execution prompt so that it preserves this projection when a handoff exists.
- Update decisions.md only with durable, high-value execution state.
- Preserve active blockers, unresolved questions, validation obligations, and strategic constraints.
- Downgrade unsupported handoff claims to assumptions or validation needs.
- Do not let handoff suggestions redefine scope, architecture, capability, or intent.
- Do not let repository convenience override projection invariants.
- Do not preserve transient implementation chatter.
- Do not generate work that violates execution invariants.
- Escalate when implementation would require changing architecture, scope, milestone boundaries, or strategic intent.
- Keep the next execution agent focused on the current operational objective while preserving long-horizon project intent.

## Projection Integrity Checklist

Before finalizing, verify:

- The projection contains resident execution-governance semantics only.
- No operational_context is included.
- No previous handoff content is included.
- No decisions.md content is included.
- No repository state is included.
- No current milestone detail is included.
- No implementation plan is included.
- No execution prompt is generated.
- Every retained statement should improve execution decisions across sessions.
- Every major retained statement traces to the Project Context or is clearly marked projection-local.
- Strategic purpose for execution is explicit.
- Execution invariants are explicit.
- Capability integrity rules are explicit.
- Architectural guardrails are explicit.
- Decision heuristics are explicit.
- Drift prevention rules are explicit.
- Authority boundary rules are explicit.
- Handoff interpretation rules are explicit.
- decisions.md preservation rules are explicit.
- Success semantics are explicit.
- Canonical vocabulary is preserved.
- Excluded operational, implementation, roadmap, audit, and milestone details are not present.
- The projection is compact enough to be injected at the start of execution-session prompt generation.
